>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":46,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":55,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":90,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Badlesmere was born about 1169, in Tong Castle, Kent, England as the daughter of Badlesmare. She married John Coningsby. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1169–":"umbes 1169–Surnud","1169–Female":"1169–Surnud","1201–1266":"1201–1266","–1327":"–1327","–Male":"Surnud","1327":"1327","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1169":"1169","1201":"1201","1266":"1266","Abt 1169":"umbes 1169","Tong Castle, Kent, England":"Tong Castle, Kent, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1169–":"noin 1169–Kuollut","1169–Female":"1169–Kuollut","1201–1266":"1201–1266","–1327":"–1327","–Male":"Kuollut","1327":"1327","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1169":"1169","1201":"1201","1266":"1266","Abt 1169":"noin 1169","Tong Castle, Kent, England":"To